entry.title: Flood Warning issued May 19 at 7:19PM CDT until May 20 at 9:00AM CDT by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
entry.summary:
Heavy rain, over a large area, has fallen in Saunders County, specifically around Prague and north of Malmo. The runoff from this rain will likely cause significant rises along Wahoo, Cottonwood, Duck, and Sand Creeks. It is possible the resulting flooding leads to water over several roads, including Highway 92 west of Wahoo and Highway 66 near Ithaca. In addition, several county roads near these creeks may flood.
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...A portion of east central Nebraska, including the following county, Saunders.
* WHEN...Until 900 AM CDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 719 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the warned area. Between 2 and 3 inches of rain have fallen. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Wahoo, Cedar Bluffs, Weston, Prague, Ithaca, Morse Bluff, Malmo, Colon, Lake Wanahoo Recreation Area and Czechland Lake.

entry.summary:
...RED FLAG WARNING IN EFFECT TODAY FROM NOON TO 8PM MDT FOR THE MIDDLE RIO GRANDE VALLEY, SANDIA AND MANZANO MOUNTAINS, AND WEST CENTRAL BASIN AND RANGE DUE TO STRONG WINDS, LOW HUMIDITY, AND HIGH FIRE DANGER...
.Another round of strong west winds and low humidity will create critical fire weather conditions this afternoon in southwestern and south-central New Mexico. Humidities will be higher than yesterday so the high fire danger will generally be limited to the southern portions of each of the zones in the Red Flag Warning. Gusty showers and an isolated storm or two may enhance winds in the Rio Grande Valley and Sandia and Manzano mountains during the afternoon hours. Winds will shift from the west to the northwest in the late afternoon behind a Pacific cold front.
* AREA AND TIMING...Middle Rio Grande Valley (Zone 106) and West Central Basin and Range (Zone 109) today from 12PM to 8PM MDT.
* 20 FOOT WINDS...West to northwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 50 mph on Monday.
* RELATIVE HUMIDITY...10 to 15 percent along and south of US 60.
* IMPACTS...Any fires that develop will likely spread rapidly. Outdoor burning is not recommended.
entry.cap:areaDesc: Middle Rio Grande Valley; West Central Basin and Range; Sandia and Manzano Mountains
